@endnode

@node "What_do" "What does the program do?"

                          @{b}Destination of program@{ub}

 NVControl is a program to control nonvolatile storage. Nonvolatile storage
is a battery backed up memory built in CD-32. It's purpose is mainly to store
game saves and config files, but it can store anything. You can also create
nonvolatile storage on Amiga with hard-drive. First you must create a directory
where you want to keep nonvolatile stores. Then you must create in
prefs/env-archive/sys file named nv_locotion. This file must contains location
of directory. For example: you created directory DH2:Games/NVStores, so nv_location
contains DH2:Games/NVStores. And one more thing - you must have
nonvolatile.library in your Libs:. This library is part of Workbench 3.1.

@endnode

@node "Description" "Description"

                               @{b}Description@{ub}

 Program can be run by clicking on its icon or from cli/shell (but then
Iconify item in menu is disabled). Program have font-sensitive GUI and
localization.

  Here goes gadgets description:

	Application	- here put application name.
	Item		- here put item name.
	Source		- opens file requester to choose source file.
			  Hotkey: s
	Destination	- opens file requester to choose destination file.
			  Hotkey: d
	Write Item	- write source file to nonvolatile storage as item
			  and application given by user.
			  Hotkey: w
	Protect Item	- protect given item of given application from
			  delete.
			  Hotkey: p
	Delete Item	- delete given item of given application from nonvolatile
			  storage.
			  Hotkey: e
	Read Item	- read given item of given appliction from nonvolatile
			  storage to destination file.
			  Hotkey: r
	Unprotect Item	- unprotect given item of given application from
			  delete.
			  Hotkey: u
	Item List	- print list of items in nonvolatile storage for given
			  application.
			  Hotkey: i

  Note: Item list have a little bug. When you use it not on CD-32 and there are
        no items for given application it prints rubbish. I really don't know
	why.

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

                                 @{b}Requirements@{ub}

  Here goes program requirements:

	- MC68020+
	- Kickstart 3.0 (V39)
	- reqtools.library 2.0 (V38)
	- Nonvolatile storage (read in @{"What does the program do" link "What_do" 0})
	- a bit of memory

@endnode

